June 20, 1991 |  Women Strike for Peace sponsored a forum on U.S. policy in the Middle East with the proceeds from the event going toward humanitarian groups aiding refugees in Iraq. Professor Parenti spoke on U.S. foreign policy during the Bush administration, saying George Bush has consistently made foreign policy decisions in line with economic policies. The goal of the U.S. in its foreign policy is to make the world safe for private corporate capital investment and private corporate capital accumulation. Thus the apparent hypocrisy of the Bush administration in tolerating totalitarianism and aggression against dissent in China while punishing aggression in the Middle East and funding civil war in Central America is actually a consistent policy of rewarding countries allowing the free conversion of resources into private capital.